<comment type="function">
<text evidence="1 2 3">Proton-dependent permease that transports di- and tripeptides as well as structurally related peptidomimetics such as aminocephalosporins into the cell. Has a clear preference for dipeptides and tripeptides composed of L-amino acids, and discriminates dipeptides on the basis of the position of charges within the substrate.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="subunit">
<text evidence="2">Monomer (Probable). Has a crown-like structure with a diameter of 8 nm and a central density.</text>
</comment>
